The deacon enters the Altar through the south door. The reader begins reading the first stasis of the 18th Kathisma (or such other kathisma as may be appointed, according to the Typicon). }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339 
\par }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339\charrsid5900090 The priest and deacon uncover their heads. }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339 
\par }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339\charrsid5900090 The curtain is closed. }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339 
\par }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339\charrsid5900090 If the Presanctified Lamb is kept in the artophorion on the Holy Table, the priest kisses the Holy Gospel Book and stands it upright behind the antimension, or lays it on the right side of
 the Holy Table. He opens the antimension, places the diskos upon it, and opens the artophorion. He places a Presanctified Lamb on the diskos with great reverence, saying nothing. The asterikos and small veil are censed and placed over the Holy Bread. The
 priest and deacon then make a prostration before the Holy Bread, and cover their }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339 heads
\par }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339\charrsid5900090 Note: If, however, the Presanctified Lamb is kept in the artophorion on the prothesis table, the priest and deacon uncover their heads. The priest and deacon go to the p
rothesis, where they make a small bow. The priest opens the artophorion and places the Presanctified Lamb on the diskos with great reverence, and then pours wine and water into the chalice as usual, saying nothing. The asterikos and veils are censed as us
u
al and placed over the Gifts, saying nothing. The priest places a standing candle before the prothesis, then takes the censer from the deacon and censes the Gifts. Then they make a prostration, while the priest says: Through the prayers of our holy father
s, 0 Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us. }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339 
\par 
\par }{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339\charrsid5900090 
Then they return to the Holy Table, and may cover their heads. In this case, the rubrics given at the second and third stasesfor the censing of the Holy Table and the transfer of the Gifts are not observed
. The curtain is opened after the transfer of the Gifts}{\cs74\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid6711339 
