\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 
\par Unto the Lord in mine affliction have I cried, and He heard me.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid7173770 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 O Lord, deliver my soul from unrighteous lips and from a crafty tongue.
\par 
\par What shall be given unto thee and what shall be added unto thee for thy crafty tongue? The arrows of the mighty one, sharpened with coals of the desert.
\par 
\par Woe is me, for my sojourning is prolonged; I have tented with the tentings of Kedar, my soul hath long been a sojourner.
\par 
\par With them that hate peace I was peaceable; when I spake unto them, they warred against me without a cause.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 Psalm 120.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 
\par I have lifted up mine eyes to the mountains, from whence cometh my help.
\par 
\par My help cometh from the Lord, Who hath made heaven and the earth.
\par 
\par Give not thy foot unto moving, and may He not slumber that keepeth thee.
\par 
\par Behold, He shall not slumber nor shall He sleep, He that keepeth Israel.
\par 
\par The Lord shall keep thee; the Lord is thy shelter at thy right hand.
\par 
\par The sun shall not burn thee by day, nor the moon by night.
\par 
\par The Lord shall keep thee from all evil, the Lord shall guard thy soul.
\par 
\par The Lord shall keep thy coming in and thy going out, from henceforth and for evermore.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 Psalm 121.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 
\par I was glad because of them that said unto me: Let us go into the house of the Lord.
\par 
\par Our feet have stood in thy courts, O Jerusalem.
\par 
\par Jerusalem is builded as a city which its dwellers share in concord.
\par 
\par For there the tribes went up, the tribes of the Lord, as a testimony for Israel, to give thanks to the name of the Lord.
\par 
\par For there are set thrones unto judgement, thrones over the house of David.
\par 
\par Ask now for the things which are for the peace of Jerusalem, and for the prosperity of them that love thee.
\par 
\par Let peace be now in thy strength, and prosperity in thy palaces.
\par 
\par For the sake of my brethren and my neighbours, I spake peace concerning thee.
\par 
\par Because of the house of the Lord our God, I have sought good things for thee.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 Psalm 122.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 
\par Unto Thee have I lifted up mine eyes, unto Thee that dwellest in heaven.
\par 
\par Behold, as the eyes of servants look unto the hands of their masters, as the eyes of the handmaid look unto the hands of her mistress, so do our eyes look unto the Lord our God, until He take pity on us.
\par 
\par Have mercy on us, O Lord, have mercy on us, for greatly are we filled with abasement.
\par 
\par Greatly hath our soul been filled therewith; let reproach come upon them that prosper, and abasement on the proud.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 Psalm 123.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7173770 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7173770\charrsid7173770 
\par Had it not been that the Lord was with us, let Israel now say, had it not been that the Lord was with us, When men rose up against us, then had they swallowed us up alive.
\par 
\par When their wrath raged against us, then had the water overwhelmed us.
\par 
\par Our soul hath passed through a torrent; then had our soul passed through the water that is irresistible.
\par 
\par Blessed be the Lord Who hath not given us to be a prey to their teeth.
\par 
\par Our soul like a sparrow was delivered out of the snare of the hunters.
\par 
\par The snare is broken, and we are delivered.
\par 
\par Our help is in the name of the Lord, Who hath made heaven and the earth.
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs53\b0\f0\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------\sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain 
\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{
\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Lord, have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs53\b0\f0\fs36\insrsid9005151 
\par }{\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 PSALM}{\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665  }{\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 24}{\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid7473308 Unto Thee, O Lord, have I lifted up my soul. 
\par 
\par O my God, in Thee have I trusted; let me never be put to shame, nor let mine enemies laugh me to scorn. 
\par 
\par Yea, let none that wait on Thee be put to shame; let them be ashamed which are lawless without a cause. 
\par 
\par Make Thy ways, O Lord, known unto me and teach me Thy paths. 
\par 
\par Lead me in Thy truth and teach me, for Thou art God my }{\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid4547475 Savior}{\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid7473308 ; for on Thee have I waited all the day long. 
\par 
\par Remember Thy compassions; O Lord, and Thy mercies, for they are from everlasting. 
\par 
\par The sins of my youth and mine ignorances remember not; according to Thy mercy remember Thou me, for the sake of Thy goodness, O Lord. 
\par 
\par Good and upright is the Lord; therefore will He set a law for them that sin in the way. 
\par 
\par He will guide the meek in }{\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid4547475 judgment}{\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid7473308 , He will teach the meek His ways. 
\par 
\par All the ways of the Lord are mercy and truth, unto them that seek after His covenant and His testimonies. 
\par 
\par For the sake of Thy name, O Lord, be gracious unto my sin; for it is great. 
\par 
\par Who is the man that feareth the Lord? He will set him a law in the way which He hath chosen. 
\par 
\par His soul shall dwell among good things, and his seed shall inherit the earth. 
\par 
\par The Lord is the strength of them that fear Him, and His covenant shall be manifested unto them. 
\par 
\par Mine eyes are ever toward the Lord, for He it is that will draw my feet out of the snare. 
\par 
\par Look upon me, and have mercy on me; for I am one only-begotten and poor. 
\par 
\par The afflictions of my heart are multiplied; bring me out from my necessities. 
\par 
\par Behold my lowliness and my toil, and forgive all my sins. 
\par 
\par Look upon my enemies, for they are multiplied, and with an unjust hatred they have hated me. 
\par 
\par Keep my soul and rescue me; let me not be put to shame, for I have hoped in Thee. 
\par 
\par The innocent and the upright have cleaved unto me, for I waited on Thee, O Lord. 
\par 
\par Redeem Israel, O God, out of all his afflictions. 
\par }\pard \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs53\b0\f0\fs36\insrsid9005151 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 PSALM}{\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665  30
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid7473308 
In Thee, O Lord, have I hoped, let me not be put to shame in the age to come; in Thy righteousness deliver me, and rescue me. 
\par 
\par Bow down Thine ear unto me, make haste to rescue me, be Thou unto me a God to defend me and a house of refuge to save me. 
\par 
\par For my strength and my refuge art Thou, and for Thy name's sake wilt Thou guide me and nourish me. 
\par 
\par Thou wilt bring me out of this snare which they have hid for me, for Thou art my defender, O Lord. 
\par 
\par Into Thy hands I will commit my spirit; Thou hast redeemed me, O Lord God of truth. 
\par 
\par Thou hast hated them that cling to empty vanities; but I have hoped in the Lord. 
\par 
\par I will rejoice and be glad in Thy mercy, for Thou hast regarded my lowliness; Thou hast saved my soul out of necessities, 
\par 
\par And hast not shut me up in the hands of enemies; Thou hast set my feet in a spacious place. 
\par 
\par Have mercy on me, O Lord, for I am afflicted; mine eye is troubled with anger, as also my soul and my belly. 
\par 
\par For my life is spent with grief, and my years with groanings; my strength hath grown weak in poverty, and my bones are troubled. 
\par 
\par I am become a reproach among all mine enemies, and greatly for my neighbors also, and a fear to mine acquaintances. They that saw me without fled from me. 
\par 
\par I am forgotten by the heart like a dead man. I am become like a broken vessel. 
\par 
\par For I have heard the reproach of many that dwell round about; when they assembled together against me, they devised to take away my life. 
\par 
\par But as for me, I have hoped in Thee, O Lord; I said: Thou art my God; in Thy hands are my lots. 
\par 
\par Deliver me from the hands of mine enemies, and from them that persecute me. 
\par 
\par Make Thy face to shine upon Thy servant, save me in Thy mercy. 
\par 
\par O Lord, let me not be put to shame, for I have called upon Thee; let the ungodly be put to shame and let them be brought down into hades. 
\par 
\par Speechless be the deceitful lips which speak iniquity against the righteous man with arrogance and contempt. 
\par 
\par How great is the multitude of Thy goodness, O Lord, which Thou hast hid for them that fear Thee, which Thou hast wrought for them that hope in Thee before the sons of men. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt hide them in the secrecy of Thy presence from the disturbance of men; Thou shalt shelter them in the tabernacle from contradiction of tongues. 
\par 
\par Blessed is the Lord, for He hath made His mercy wondrous in a fortified city. 
\par 
\par But as for me, I said in mine ecstasy: I am cast away from the presence of Thine eyes. Therefore hast Thou heard the voice of my supplication when I cried unto Thee. 
\par 
\par O love ye the Lord, all ye His saints, for the Lord requireth truth; and unto them that act with exceeding pride, He rendereth them their due. 
\par 
\par Be ye manful, and let your heart be strengthened, all ye that hope in the Lord. 
\par }\pard \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 PSALM}{\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665  90
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 He that dwelleth in the help of the Most High shall abide in the shelter of the God of heaven. 
\par He shall say unto the Lord: Thou art my helper and my refuge. He is my God, and I will hope in Him. 
\par For He shall deliver thee from the snare of the hunters and from every troubling word. 
\par With His shoulders will He overshadow thee, and under His wings shalt thou have hope. 
\par With a shield will His truth encompass thee; thou shalt not be afraid for the terror by night, nor for the arrow that flieth by day, 
\par Nor for the thing that walketh in darkness, nor for the mishap and demon of noonday. 
\par A thousand shall fall at thy side, and ten thousand at thy right hand, but unto thee shall it not come nigh. 
\par Only with thine eyes shalt thou behold, and thou shalt see the reward of sinners. 
\par For Thou, O Lord, art my hope. Thou madest the Most High thy refuge; 
\par No evils shall come nigh thee, and no scourge shall draw nigh unto thy dwelling. 
\par For He shall give His angels charge over thee, to keep thee in all thy ways. 
\par On their hands shall they bear thee up, lest at any time thou dash thy foot against a stone. 
\par Upon the asp and basilisk shalt thou tread, and thou shalt trample upon the lion and dragon. 
\par For he hath set his hope on Me, and I will deliver him; I will shelter him because he hath known My name. 
\par He shall cry unto Me, and I will hearken unto him. I am with him in affliction, and I will rescue him and glorify him. 
\par With length of days will I satisfy him, and I will show him My salvation. }{\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
