The bodiless nature of the Cherubim * with unceasing hymns glorify Thee. * The six-wi
nged beings, the Seraphim, * with never-ceasing voices supremely exalt Thee. * And all the ranks of the Angels * praise Thee with thrice-holy hymns. * For before all art Thou the existing Father, * and Thou hast Thy co-unoriginate Son; * and bearing the c
o
-honorable Spirit of life, * Thou dost manifest the Indivisible Trinity. * O Most holy Virgin Mother of God, * and ye eyewitnesses of the Word and servants, * all the choirs both of Prophets and Martyrs, * as those that have attained unto life immortal, *
 supplicate earnestly for us all, * for we all are in distress; * that, being delivered from the delusion of the evil one, * we may cry out the angelic hymn: Holy, Holy, Holy, Thrice-holy Lord, * have mercy and save us. Amen.}{
\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 
\par And immediately, in a lower voice, the reader:
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
I believe in one God, the Father Almighty, Maker of heaven and the earth and of all things visible and invisible. And in one Lord Jesus Christ, the Son of God, the Only-begotten, begotten of the Father before all ages; Light of Li
ght, true God of true God; begotten, not made; of one essence with the Father, by Whom all things were made; Who for us men and for our salvation came down from the heavens, and was incarnate of the Holy Spirit and the Virgin Mary, and became man; And was
 
crucified for us under Pontius Pilate, and suffered and was buried; And arose again on the third day according to the Scriptures; And ascended into the heavens, and sitteth at the right hand of the Father; And shall come again, with glory, to judge both t
h
e living and the dead; Whose kingdom shall have no end. And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord, the Giver of life; Who proceedeth from the Father; Who with the Father and the Son together is worshipped and glorified; Who spake by the prophets. In One, Holy, Cat
holic, and Apostolic Church. I confess one baptism for the remission of sins. I look for the resurrection of the dead, And the life of the age to come. Amen. 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And immediately, \'93O most holy Lady\'85\'94; all are said twice except the first verse, \'93O most holy Lady\'85\'94
, which is said Thrice. The verses are alternated by each choir.
\par And with each one we make a prostration, except on Friday evenings, when this is read instead of being chanted, we make a bow:
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O most holy Lady Theotokos, intercede for us sinners.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O all ye Heavenly Host of the holy Angels and Archangels, intercede for us sinners.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Twice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O holy John, Prophet and Forerunner and Baptist of our Lord Jesus Christ, intercede for us sinners.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Twice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O holy glorious Apostles, Prophets, and Martyrs, and all the Saints, intercede for us sinners}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 .}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Twice)}{
\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O our holy and God-bearing fathers, pastors, and ecumenical teachers, intercede for us sinners.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Twice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (patron saint of the temple),}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 intercede for us sinners.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{
\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Twice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Invincible and incomprehensible and divine power of the precious and life-giving Cross, forsake not us sinners.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Twice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 

\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O God, cleanse us sinners.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Twice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O God, cleanse us sinners, and have mercy on us.
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then the reader: 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake.}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Lord have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Our Father
, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed be Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors; and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from th
e evil one.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  For Thine is the Kingdom, and the power, and the glory; of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Amen.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
