On Monday and Wednesday evenings, in the Second Tone:
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Enlighten mine eyes, O Christ God, lest at any time I sleep unto death, lest at any time mine enemy say: I have prevailed against him.
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par Be my soul\rquote s helper, O God, for I pass through the midst of many snares; deliver me out of them, and save me, O Good One, for Thou art the Lover of Mankind.
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Theotokion: 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 
Seeing that we have no boldness on account of our many sins, do thou beseech Him that was born of thee, O Virgin Theotokos for the supplication of a mother availeth much to win the Master's favor. Disdain not the prayers of sinne
rs, O all-pure one, for merciful and mighty to save is He Who deigned also to suffer for our sake.
\par }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6953665 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
On Tuesday and Thursday evenings, these troparia, in the Eighth Tone:}{\insrsid7473308\charrsid9316926 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Lord, Thou knowest the unsleeping vigilance of mine invisible enemies, 
and the weakness of my miserable flesh knowest Thou Who hast fashioned me: Into Thy hands, therefore, I will commit my spirit; shelter me with the wings of Thy goodness, lest at any time I sleep unto death, and enlighten the eyes of my mind to the enjoyme
nt of Thy divine words, and raise me up in a seasonable time unto Thy glorification, for Thou alone art good and the Lover of mankind.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Stichos:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Look upon me and hear me, O Lord my God.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 How terrible is Thy judgment, O Lord, with the angels standing round abo
ut, the men being led in, the books opened, the deeds examined, the thoughts weighed. What judgment shall be awarded unto me who was conceived in sins? Who shall quench the flame for me, who shall enlighten the darkness for me, if not Thou, O Lord Who has
t mercy on me, as the Lover of mankind.}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Grant me tears, O God, as Thou didst once give to the sinning woman, and vouchsafe me to moisten Thy feet which have freed me from the path of delusion, and
 to offer to Thee as fragrant myrrh a pure life, fashioned in me by repentance, that I may hear Thy desired voice: Thy faith hath saved thee, go in peace.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs36\insrsid7473308 {\field{\*\fldinst SYMBOL 174 \\f "Symbol" \\s 18}{\fldrslt\f3\fs36}}}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The
otokion:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 
Having in thee, O Theotokos, a hope that cannot be put to shame, I shall be saved; having obtained thy mediation, O most pure one, I shall not fear. I shall pursue enemies and triumph over them, having covered myself, as in a breastplate, only wit
h thy protection; and imploring thine all-powerful aid, I cry unto thee: O Sovereign Lady, save me through thine intercessions, and raise me up from somber sleep to thy glorification, by the might of the Son of God who was incarnate of thee.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2229485 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 On Friday evenings, the troparion of the Saturday commemoration
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid8747982 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs56\i\f1\insrsid2229485 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8747982\charrsid8747982 And after the Troparia: 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader:}{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  Lord have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Forty Times)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim; who without corruption gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Through the prayers of our holy fathers, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us. 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Amen. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8747982 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 And this prayer of Basil the Great:
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader:}{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
 O Lord, O Lord, Who hast delivered us from every arrow that flieth by day, deliver us from everything that walketh in darkness. Receive as an evening sacrifice the lifting up o
f our hands. Vouchsafe us also to pass through the course of the night without blemish, untempted by evil. And deliver us from every anxiety and fear that come to us from the devil. Grant unto our souls compunction, and unto our thoughts solicitude concer
n
ing the trial at Thy dread and righteous judgment. Nail down our flesh with the fear of Thee, and mortify our earthly members, that in quietness of sleep we may be enlightened by the vision of Thy judgments. Take from us every unseemly dream and perniciou
s
 carnal desire. Raise us up at the hour of prayer, fortified in faith and advancing in Thy commandments; through the benevolence and goodness of Thine Only-begotten Son, with Whom Thou art blessed, together with Thy most-holy and good and life creating Sp
irit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par O come, let us worship God our King. 
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and God. 
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ Himself, our King and God}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 . 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs53\b0\f0\fs36\insrsid7473308 PSALM 50 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid7473308 Have m
ercy on me, O God, according to Thy great mercy; and according to the multitude of Thy compassions blot out my transgression. 
\par 
\par Wash me thoroughly from mine iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin. 
\par 
\par For I know mine iniquity, and my sin is ever before me. 
\par 
\par Against Thee only have I sinned and done this evil before Thee, that Thou mightest be justified in Thy words, and prevail when Thou art judged. 
\par 
\par For behold, I was conceived in iniquities, and in sins did my mother bear me. 
\par 
\par For behold, Thou hast loved truth; the hidden and secret things of Thy wisdom hast Thou made manifest unto me. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt sprinkle me with hyssop, and I shall be made clean; Thou shalt wash me, and I shall be made whiter than snow. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt make me to hear joy and gladness; the bones that be humbled, they shall rejoice. 
\par 
\par Turn Thy face away from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities. 
\par 
\par Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me. 
\par 
\par Cast me not away from Thy presence, and take not Thy Holy Spirit from me. 
\par 
\par Restore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, and with Thy governing Spirit establish me. 
\par 
\par I shall teach transgressors Thy ways, and the ungodly shall turn back unto Thee. 
\par 
\par Deliver me from blood-guiltiness, O God, Thou God of my salvation; my tongue shall rejoice in Thy righteousness. 
\par 
\par O Lord, Thou shalt open my lips, and my mouth shall declare Thy praise. 
\par 
\par For if Thou hadst desired sacrifice, I had given it; with whole-burnt offerings Thou shalt not be pleased. 
\par 
\par A sacrifice unto God is a broken spirit; a heart that is broken and humbled God will not despise. 
\par 
\par Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded. 
\par 
\par Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and whole-burnt offerings. 
\par 
\par Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par }\pard \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs53\b0\f0\fs36\insrsid9005151 
\par }\pard \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8747982 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 PSALM 101}{\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8747982 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid8747982\charrsid8747982 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b0\i0\cf0\cgrid0\noproof0\insrsid7473308 O Lord, hear my prayer, and let my cry come unto Thee. 
\par 
\par Turn not Thy face away from me; in the day when I am afflicted, incline Thine ear unto me. 
\par 
\par In the day when I call upon Thee, quickly hearken unto me. 
\par 
\par For my days are vanished like smoke, and my bones consumed like wood for the burning. 
\par 
\par I am smitten like grass, and withered is my heart, for I forgot to eat my bread. 
\par 
\par By reason of the voice of my groaning, my bone hath cleaved unto my flesh. 
\par 
\par I am become like a pelican of the wilderness, I am like an owl in a ruined house. 
\par 
\par I have watched, and am like a sparrow that sitteth alone upon the house-top. 
\par 
\par The whole day long mine enemies reproached me, and they that praised me made an oath against me. 
\par 
\par For before the face of Thy wrath and Thine anger I ate ashes like bread, and my drink I mingled with weeping; for after uplifting me, Thou hast dashed me down. 
\par 
\par My days like a shadow have declined, and I like grass am withered. 
\par 
\par But Thou, O Lord, for ever abidest, and Thy remembrance is unto generation and generation. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt rise up and have pity upon Sion, for it is time to have compassion on her, yea, the time is come. 
\par 
\par For Thy servants have taken pleasure in her stones, and they shall feel pity for her dust. 
\par 
\par And the nations shall fear Thy name, O Lord, and all the kings of the earth Thy glory. 
\par 
\par For the Lord shall build up Sion, and He shall be seen in His glory. 
\par 
\par He hath regarded the prayer of the humble, and hath not despised their supplication. 
\par 
\par Let this be written for another generation, and the people that is being created shall praise the Lord. 
\par 
\par For He hath looked out from His holy height, the Lord from heaven hath looked upon the earth, 
\par 
\par To hear the groaning of them that be in fetters, to loose the sons of the slain, 
\par 
\par To declare in Sion the name of the Lord, and His praise in Jerusalem, 
\par 
\par When the peoples are gathered together, and the kings to serve the Lord. 
\par 
\par He answered Him in the way of his strength: The fewness of my days declare unto me. 
\par 
\par Take me not away at the half of my days; in generations and generations are Thy years. 
\par 
\par In the beginning, O Lord, Thou didst lay the foundation of the earth, and the heavens are the works of Thy hands. 
\par 
\par They shall perish, but Thou abidest; and all like a garment shall grow old, 
\par 
\par And as a vesture shalt Thou fold them, and they shall be changed; but Thou art the same, and Thy years shall not fail. 
\par 
\par The sons of Thy servants shall have their dwelling, and their seed for ever shall be guided aright.
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid9178099 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain 
\s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 The Prayer of Manasses, King of Judea: 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O Lord Almighty, the God of our fathers, of Abraham, and Isaac, and Jacob, and of their righteous seed; 
\par Who hast made heaven and the earth with all their majesty; Who hast bound the sea by the word of Thy commandment; 
\par Who hast closed the abyss, and sealed it by Thy terrible and glorious name; of Whom all things are afraid, and tremble from the presence of Thy might; 
\par for no one can endure the majesty of Thy glory, and unbearable is the wrath of Thy threatening toward sinners, but immeasurable and unsearchable is the mercifulness of Thy promise; 
\par for Thou art the Lord most High, compassionate, long-suffering, and plenteous in mercy, and repentest of the evils of men: 
\par Thou, O Lord, according to the multitude of Thy goodness, hast promised penitence and forgiveness to them that have sinned against Thee, and in the multitude of Thy compassions hast decreed repentance for the salvation of sinners. }{
\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid9178099 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Thou, therefore, O Lord God of hosts, hast not appointed repentance for the righteous, for Abraham and Isaac and Jacob, who have not sinned against Thee, but hast laid repentance upon me a sinner, for I have sinned more
 than the number of the sands of the sea. 
\par Mine iniquities are multiplied, and I am not worthy to look upon and to see the height of heaven for the multitude of mine iniquities. 
\par For I am bowed down with many iron bands so that I cannot lift up my head, and there is no release for me, because I have provoked Thine anger, and done evil before Thee, neither having done Thy will, nor having kept Thy commandments; 
\par and now I bow the knees of my heart, beseeching of Thee clemency. 
\par I have sinned, O Lord, I have sinned, and I know mine iniquities; but imploring I pray Thee: Loose me, O Lord, loose me, and destroy me not with mine iniquities. 
\par Neither in enmity forever keep mine evils, neither condemn me to the nethermost parts of the earth. 
\par For Thou, O God, art the God of them that repent, and upon me Thou wilt show all Thy goodness; for Thou shalt save me who am unworthy, according to the plenitude of Thy mercy, 
\par and I will praise Thee continually throughout the days of my life: for all the heavenly hosts hymn Thee, and Thine is the glory unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9178099 {\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid9178099 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Lord have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed be Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And le
ad us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  For Thine is the Kingdom, and the power, and the glory; of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Amen. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid9178099 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 
And these }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid4547475 Troparia}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308  in the Sixth Tone: 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Have mercy on us, O Lord, have mercy on us; * for at loss for any defense, * this prayer do we sinners offer unto thee as Master: have mercy on us.}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Lord, ha
ve mercy on us; * for we have hoped in Thee, be not angry with us greatly, * neither remember our iniquities; * but look upon us now as Thou art compassionate, * and deliver us from our enemies, * for Thou art our God, and we, Thy people; * all are the wo
rks of Thy hands, and we call upon Thy name.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308\charrsid9005151 Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Theotokion:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 The door of compassion open unto us, * O blessed Theotokos, * for hoping in the
e, let us not perish; * through thee may we be delivered from adversities, * for thou art the salvation of the Christian race}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 .
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader:}{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  Lord have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Forty Times)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim; who without corruption gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 In the name of the Lord, father (master) bless.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Through the prayers of our holy fathers, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us. 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Amen. 
\par O Sovereign God, the Father Almighty, O Lord, the Only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ, and O Holy Spirit, one Godhead, one Power: Have mercy on me a si
nner, and by the judgments which Thou knowest, save me, Thine unworthy servant; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par O come, let us worship God our King. 
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and God. 
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ Himself, our King and God. 
\par 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Psalm 69 is omitted at this point when the Great Canon is read in the First Week of Great Lent)
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 PSALM 69 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O God, be attentive unto helping me; O Lord, make haste to help me. 
\par Let them be shamed and confounded that seek after my soul. 
\par Let them be turned back and brought to shame that desire evils against me. 
\par Let them be turned back straightway in shame that say unto me: Well done! Well done! 
\par Let them be glad and rejoice in Thee all that seek after Thee, O God, and let them that love Thy salvation say continually: The Lord be magnified.
\par But as for me, I am poor and needy; O God, come unto mine aid. 
\par My helper and my deliverer art Thou, O Lord; make no long tarrying.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs53\b0\f0\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par PSALM 142 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O Lord, hear my prayer, give ear unto my supplication in Thy truth; hearken unto me in Thy righteousness. 
\par And enter not into }{\f1\fs32\insrsid4547475 judgment}{\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  with Thy servant, for in Thy sight shall no man living be justified. 
\par For the enemy hath persecuted my soul; he hath humbled my life down to the earth. 
\par He hath sat me in darkness as those that have been long dead, and my spirit within me is become despondent; within me my heart is troubled. 
\par I remembered days of old, I meditated on all Thy works, I pondered on the creations of Thy hands. 
\par I stretched forth my hands unto Thee; my soul thirsteth after Thee like a waterless land. 
\par Quickly hear me, O Lord; my spirit hath fainted away. 
\par Turn not Thy face away from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit. 
\par 
\par Cause me to hear Thy mercy in the morning; for in Thee have I put my hope. 
\par Cause me to know, O Lord, the way wherein I should walk; for unto Thee have I lifted up my soul. 
\par Rescue me from mine enemies, O Lord; unto Thee have I fled for refuge. Teach me to do Thy will, for Thou art my God. 
\par Thy good Spirit shall lead me in the land of uprightness; for Thy name's sake, O Lord, shalt Thou quicken me. 
\par In Thy righteousness shalt Thou bring my soul out of affliction, and in Thy mercy shalt Thou utterly destroy mine enemies. 
\par And Thou shalt cut off all them that afflict my soul, for I am Thy servant.}{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs53\b0\f0\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par THE DOXOLOGY
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Read, not sung) 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader:}{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  Glory to God in the highest, and on earth, peace and good will among men. 
\par We praise Thee, we bless Thee, we worship Thee, we glorify Thee, we give thanks to Thee for Thy great glory. 
\par O Lord, heavenly King, God the Father Almighty; O Lord, the only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ; and O Holy Spirit. O Lord God, Lamb of God, Son of the Fath
er, that takest away the sin of the world; have mercy on us; Thou that takest away the sins of the world, receive our prayer; Thou that sittest at the right hand of the Father, have mercy on us. 
\par For Thou only art holy; Thou only art the Lord, O Jesus Christ, to the glory of God the Father. Amen. 
\par Every night will I bless Thee, and I will praise Thy Name forever, yea, forever and forever. 
\par Lord, thou hast been our refuge in generation and generation. 
\par I said: O Lord, have mercy on me, heal my soul, for I have sinned against Thee. 
\par O Lord, unto Thee have I fled for refuge, teach me to do Thy will, for Thou art my God. 
\par For in Thee is the fountain of life, in Thy light shall we see light. 
\par O continue Thy mercy unto them that know Thee. 
\par Vouchsafe, O Lord, to keep us this night without sin. 
\par Blessed art Thou, O Lord, the God of our Fathers, and praised and glorified is Thy name unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par Let Thy mercy, O Lord, be upon us, according as we have hoped in Thee. 
\par Blessed art Thou, O Lord, teach me Thy statutes. 
\par Blessed art Thou, O Master, give me understanding of Thy statutes. 
\par Blessed art Thou, O Holy One, enlighten me by Thy statutes. 
\par O Lord, Thy mercy endureth forever; disdain not the works of Thy hands. 
\par To Thee is due praise, to Thee is due a song, to Thee glory is due, to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 After this, if it is not the first week of Lent, we say a canon to a saint of the commemor
ative cycle (from the Menaion), or to the Theotokos (from the Octoechos). And after the completion of the canon and stichera, we chant: 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir: }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 It is truly meet to bless thee, the Theotokos, ever blessed and most blameless, and Mother of our God. More hono
rable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim, who without corruption gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify. }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Prostration.}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 

\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs56\i\f1\insrsid2229485 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  

\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par Lord have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par Our Father, Who art in the 
Heavens, hallowed be Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.}{
\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  For Thine is the Kingdom, and the power, and the glory; of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Amen. 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2229485 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2229485 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then we chant in a loud voice, and slowly, in the Sixth Tone (except on Fr
iday evenings we omit this entirely and say the Kontakion of the Saturday commemoration): 
\par }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir: }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Lord of hosts, be with us, * for beside Thee, * we have no other helper in adversity; * O Lord of hosts, have mercy on us.}{
\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502  
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (If there be two choirs, the second choir repeateth)
\par And the first choir chanteth the stichos and refrain:}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 
\par Stichos 1:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Praise ye God in His saints, praise Him in the firmament of His power.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Lord of hosts, be with us\'85}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And the second choir:}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665  
\par Stichos 2:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Praise Him for His mighty acts, praise Him}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  according }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 to the multitude of His greatness.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 

\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Lord of hosts, be with us\'85}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid13855502 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The first choir:}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665  
\par Stichos 3:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Praise Him with the sound of Trumpet, praise Him with the psaltery and harp.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 O Lord of hosts, be with us\'85
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The second choir:}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665  
\par Stichos 4:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Praise Him with timbrel and dance, praise Him with strings and flute.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Lord of hosts, be with us\'85}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The first choir:}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665  
\par Stichos 5:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Praise Him with tuneful cymbals, praise Him with cymbals of jubilation. Let every breath praise the Lord.}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 O Lord of hosts, be with us\'85
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then both choirs, having come down from the kleros together, chant this stichos:
\par Stichos 6: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Praise ye God in His saints, praise Him in the firmament of His power.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Lord of hosts, be with us\'85}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid13855502 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O Lord, if we had not had Thy saints as intercessors, * and Thy goodness being merciful to us, * how should we have dared, O Savior, to hymn Thee, * Whom angels do
 unceasingly glorify? * O Thou that knowest the hearts, spare our souls.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Greatly multiplied, O Theotokos, are my sins, * and unto thee have I fled, O pure one, * imploring salvation. * Do thou visit mine 
enfeebled soul, * and pray to thy Son and our God * that He grant me forgiveness for the evil I have done, O thou only blessed one.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid13046292 
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 O all-holy Theotokos, * throughout my lifetime forsake me not, * to human protection entrust me not, * but do thou thyself defend me and have mercy on me.
\par }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6953665 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8260773 {\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 All my hope I place in thee, * O Mother of God, * keep me under thy protection.}{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid8260773 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8260773 {\f1\fs32\insrsid13046292 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Lord, have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (forty times) 
\par }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 The Prayer of the Hours: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
Thou Who at all times and every hour, in heaven and on e
arth, art worshipped and glorified, O Christ God, Who art long-suffering, plenteous in mercy, most compassionate, Who loveth the righteous and hast mercy on sinners, Who callest all to salvation through the promise of good things to come: Receive, O Lord,
 
our prayers at this hour, and guide our life toward Thy commandments. Sanctify our souls, make chaste our bodies, correct our thoughts, purify our intentions, and deliver us from every sorrow, evil and pain. Compass us about with Thy holy angels, that, gu
arded and guided by their array, we may attain to the unity of the faith and the knowledge of Thine unapproachable glory; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par Lord have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim; who without corruption gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify. 
\par In the name of the Lord, father (master) bless.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Through the prayers of our holy fathers, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us.
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Amen. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And then the Prayer of St. Ephraim the Syrian 
\par (on Friday evenings, the prayer of St. Ephraim is not said):
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 The Prayer of St. Ephraim the Syrian
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  O Lord and Master of my life, a spirit of idleness, despondency, ambition, and idle talking give me not. 

\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Prostration
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest: }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 But rather a spirit of chastity, humble-mindedness, patience, and love bestow upon me Thy servant. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Prostration}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest: }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 Yea, O Lord King, grant me to see my own failings and not condemn my brother; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Prostration}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then twelve reverences. With each one we say:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest: }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 O God, cleanse me a sinner.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then, the entire prayer without a break:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest: }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
O Lord and Master of my life, a spirit of idleness, despondency, ambition, and idle talking give me not. But rather a spirit of chastity, humble-mindedness, patience, and love bestow upon m
e Thy servant. Yea, O Lord King, grant me to see my own failings and not condemn my brother; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Prostration
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13046292 {\f1\fs32\insrsid13046292 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then the Reader immediately continues with the  Trisagion:  }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{
\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master,}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par Lord have mercy.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed be Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us}{
\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 not into}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  For Thine is the Kingdom, and the power, and the glory; of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\cs56\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Reader: }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Amen. Lord, have mercy}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 .}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 (Twelve times)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 Save, help, and protect us, O Virgin Theotokos}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 . 
\par \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 
The Supplicatory Prayer to the Most Holy Theotokos, of Paul the monk of the Monastery of Evergetides (Of the Benefactress)
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O undefiled, untainted, uncorrupted, most pure, chaste Virgin, Thou Bride of God and Sovereign L
ady, who didst unite the Word of God to mankind through thy most glorious birth giving, and hast linked the apostate nature of our race with the heavenly; who art the only hope of the hopeless, and the helper of the struggling, the ever-ready protection o
f
 them that hasten unto thee, and the refuge of all Christians: Do not shrink with loathing from me a sinner, defiled, who with polluted thoughts, words, and deeds have made myself utterly unprofitable, and through slothfulness of mind have become a slave 
t
o the pleasures of life. But as the Mother of God Who loveth mankind, show thy love for mankind and mercifully have compassion upon me a sinner and prodigal, and accept my supplication, which is offered to thee out of my defiled mouth; and making use of t
h
y motherly boldness, entreat thy Son and our Master and Lord that He may be pleased to open for me the bowels of His loving kindness and graciousness to mankind, and, disregarding my numberless offenses, will turn me back to repentance, and show me to be 
a
 tried worker of His precepts. And be thou ever present unto me as merciful, compassionate and well disposed; in the present life be thou a fervent intercessor and helper, repelling the assaults of adversaries and guiding me to salvation, and at the time 
o
f my departure taking care of my miserable soul, and driving far away from it the dark countenances of the evil demons; lastly, at the dreadful day of judgment delivering me from torment eternal and showing me to be an heir of the ineffable glory of thy S
o
n and our God; all of which may I attain, O my Sovereign Lady, most holy Theotokos, in virtue of thine intercession and protection, through the grace and love to mankind of thine only begotten Son, our Lord and God and Savior, Jesus Christ, to Whom is due
 all glory, honor and worship, together with His unoriginate Father, and His Most Holy and good and life creating Spirit, now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen.}{\cs55\b\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308  
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Another Prayer; to our Lord Jesus Christ, by Antiochus the monk 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 And grant unto us, O Mast
er, in the coming sleep, rest for body and soul, and preserve us from the gloomy slumber of sin, and from every dark and nocturnal sensuality. Subdue the impulses of passions, extinguish the fiery darts of the evil one that are cunningly hurled against us
,
 assuage the rebellions of our flesh, and every earthly and fleshly subtlety of ours lull to sleep. And grant unto us, O God, a watchful mind, chaste thought, a sober heart, a sleep gentle and free from every satanic illusion. Raise us up at the time of p
r
ayer firmly grounded in Thy judgments. All the night long grant us a doxology, that we may hymn and bless and glorify Thy most honorable and majestic name: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Ame
n. 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13046292 {\f1\fs32\insrsid13046292 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 At this point, according the to usage of Holy Trinity Monastery, the Prayers approaching sleep are said.
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 If these prayers are not to be said at this time, skip to page 4}{
\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7354112 8}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 .}{\insrsid7473308 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8747982 
\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayers Approaching Sleep 
\par }\pard \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 
\par Prayer I, of St. Macarius the Great. 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Eternal God and King of all creation, Who hast vouchsafed me to arrive at this hour, forgive me the sins that I have committed this day in deed, word, and thought; and cleanse, O Lord, my lowly soul of all impurity o
f flesh and spirit, and grant me, O Lord, to pass the sleep of this night in peace; that, rising from my lowly bed, I may please Thy most holy name all the days of my life, and thwart the enemies, fleshly and bodiless, that war against me. And deliver me,
 O Lord, from vain thoughts and evil desires which defile me. For Thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now, and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f176\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer II, of St. Antiochus:
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Rul
er of all, Word of the Father, O Jesus Christ, Thou Who art perfect: for the sake of the plenitude of Thy mercy, never depart from me, but always remain in me, Thy servant. O Jesus, Good Shepherd of Thy sheep, deliver me not over to the sedition of the se
r
pent, and leave me not to the will of Satan, for the seed of corruption is in me. But do Thou, O Lord, worshipful God, Holy King, Jesus Christ, as I sleep, guard me by the Unwaning Light, Thy Holy Spirit, by Whom Thou didst sanctify Thy disciples. O Lord,
 
grant me, thine unworthy servant, Thy salvation upon my bed. Enlighten my mind with the light of understanding of Thy Holy Gospel; my soul, with the love of Thy Cross; my heart, with the purity of Thy word; my body, with Thy passionless passion. Keep my t
houghts in Thy humility, and raise me up at the proper time for Thy glorification. For most glorified art Thou together with Thine unoriginate Father, and the Most Holy Spirit, unto the ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f176\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer III, to the Most Holy Spirit:
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Lord, Heavenly Kin
g, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, show compassion and have mercy on me, Thy sinful servant, and loose me from mine unworthiness, and forgive all wherein I have sinned against Thee today as a man, and not only as a man, but even worse than a beast, my sins vo
l
untary and involuntary, known and unknown, whether from youth, and from evil suggestion, or whether from brazenness and despondency. If I have sworn by Thy name, or blasphemed it in my thoughts; or grieved anyone, or have become angry about anything; or h
a
ve lied, or slept needlessly, or if a beggar hath come to me and I disdained him; or if I have grieved my brother, or have quarreled, or have condemned anyone; or if I have been boastful, or prideful, or angry; if, as I stood at prayer, my mind hath been 
d
istracted by the wiles of this world, or by thoughts of depravity; if I have overeaten, or have drunk excessively, or laughed frivolously; if I have thought evil, or have seen the beauty of another and been wounded thereby in my heart; if I have said impr
o
per things, or derided my brother's sin when mine own sins are countless; if I have been neglectful of prayer, or have done some other wrong that I cannot remember, for all of this and more than this have I done: have mercy, O Master my Creator, on me Thy
 
downcast and unworthy servant, and loose me, and remit, and forgive me, for Thou art good and the Lover of mankind, so that, lustful, sinful, and wretched as I am, I may lie down and sleep and rest in peace. And I shall worship, and hymn, and glorify Thy 
most honorable name, together with the Father and His Only-begotten Son, now and ever, and unto the ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\tx2520\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f176\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer IV, of St. Macarius the Great
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par What shall I offer Thee, or what shall I give Thee, O greatly-gifted, immortal King, O compassionate Lord 
Who lovest mankind? For though I have been slothful in pleasing Thee, and have done nothing good, Thou hast led me to the close of this day that is past, establishing the conversion and salvation of my soul. Be merciful to me a sinner, bereft of every goo
d
 deed, raise up my fallen soul which hath become defiled by countless sins, and take away from me every evil thought of this visible life. Forgive my sins, O Only Sinless One, in which I have sinned against Thee this day, known or unknown, in word, and de
e
d, and thought and in all my senses. Do Thou Thyself protect and guard me from every opposing circumstance, by Thy Divine authority and power and inexpressible love for mankind. Blot out, O God, blot out the multitude of my sins. Be pleased, O Lord, to de
l
iver me from the net of the Evil One, and save my passionate soul, and overshadow me with the light of Thy countenance when Thou shalt come in glory; and cause me, uncondemned now, to sleep a dreamless sleep, and keep Thy servant untroubled by thoughts, a
n
d drive away from me all satanic deeds; and enlighten for me the eyes of my heart with understanding, lest I sleep unto death. And send me an angel of peace, a guardian and guide of my soul and body, that he may deliver me from mine enemies; that, rising 
f
rom my bed, I may offer Thee prayers of thanksgiving. Yea, O Lord, hearken unto me, Thy sinful and wretched servant, in confession and conscience; grant me, when I arise, to be instructed by Thy sayings; and through Thine angels cause demonic despondency 
t
o be driven far from me: that I may bless Thy holy name, and glorify and extol the most pure Theotokos Mary, whom Thou hast given to us sinners as a protectress, and accept her who prayeth for us. For I know that she exemplifieth Thy love for mankind and 
prayeth for us without ceasing. Through her protection, and the sign of the precious Cross, and for the sake of all Thy saints, preserve my wretched soul, O Jesus Christ our God: for holy art Thou, and most glorious for ever. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f176\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer V
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Lord our God
, as Thou art good and the Lover of mankind, forgive me wherein I have sinned today in word, deed, and thought. Grant me peaceful and undisturbed sleep; send Thy guardian angel to protect and keep me from evil. For Thou art the Guardian of our souls and b
odies, and unto Thee do we send up glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer VI
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Lord our God, in Whom we believe and Whose Name we invoke above every name, grant us, as we go to 
sleep, relaxation of soul and body, and keep us from all dreams, and dark pleasures; stop the onslaught of the passions and quench the burnings that arise in the flesh. Grant us to live chastely in deed and word, that we may obtain a virtuous life, and no
t fall away from Thy promised blessings; for blessed art Thou for ever. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 
Prayer VII, of St. John Chrysostom, according to the number of hours of day and night: 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f176\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O Lord, deprive me not of Thy heavenly good things. 
\par O Lord, deliver me from the eternal torments. 
\par O Lord, if I have sinned in mind or thought, in word or deed, forgive me. 
\par O Lord, deliver me from all ignorance, forgetfulness, faint-heartedness, and stony insensibility. 
\par O Lord, deliver me from every temptation. 
\par O Lord, enlighten my heart which evil desire hath darkened. 
\par O Lord, as a man I have sinned, but do Thou, as the compassionate God, have mercy on me, seeing the infirmity of my soul. 
\par O Lord, send Thy grace to my help, that I may glorify Thy holy name. 
\par O Lord Jesus Christ, write me Thy servant in the Book of Life, and grant me a good end. 
\par O Lord my God, even though I have done nothing good in Thy sight, yet grant me by Thy grace to make a good beginning. 
\par O Lord, sprinkle into my heart the dew of Thy grace. 
\par O Lord of heaven and earth, remember me Thy sinful servant, shameful and unclean, in Thy kingdom. Amen.
\par 
\par O Lord, accept me in penitence. 
\par O Lord, forsake me not. O Lord, lead me not into temptation. 
\par O Lord, grant me good thoughts. 
\par O Lord, grant me tears, and remembrance of death, and compunction. 
\par O Lord, grant me the thought of confessing my sins. 
\par O Lord, grant me humility, chastity, and obedience. 
\par O Lord, grant me patience, courage, and meekness. 
\par O Lord, implant in me the root of good, Thy fear in my heart. 
\par O Lord, vouchsafe me to love Thee with all my soul and thoughts, and in all things to do Thy will. 
\par O Lord, protect me from evil men, and demons, and passions, and from every other unseemly thing. 
\par O Lord, Thou knowest that Thou doest as Thou wilt: Thy will be done also in me a sinner; for blessed art Thou unto the ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer VIII, to our Lord Jesus Christ
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Lord Jesus Christ, Son of God, for the sake of Thy most honorable Mother, and Thy bodiless angels, Thy Prophet and Forerunner an
d Baptist, the God-inspired apostles, the radiant and victorious martyrs, the holy and God-bearing fathers, and through the intercessions of all the saints, deliver me from the besetting presence of the demons. Yea, my Lord and Creator, Who desirest not t
h
e death of the sinner, but rather that he be converted and live, grant conversion also to me, wretched and unworthy; rescue me from the mouth of the pernicious serpent, who is yawning to devour me and take me down to Hades alive. Yea, my Lord, my Comfort,
 
Who for my miserable sake wast clothed in corruptible flesh, draw me out of misery, and grant comfort to my miserable soul. Implant in my heart to fulfill Thy commandments, and to forsake evil deeds, and to obtain Thy blessings; for in Thee, O Lord, have 
I hoped, save me.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 
\par }{\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\insrsid394076 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 
Prayer IX, to the Most Holy Theotokos
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O good Mother of the Good King, most pure and blessed Theotokos Mary, do thou pour out the mercy of thy Son and our God upon my passionate soul, and by thine inter
cessions guide me unto good works, that I may pass the remaining time of my life without blemish, and attain paradise through thee, O Virgin Theotokos, who alone art pure and blessed.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 Prayer X, to the Holy Guardian Angel}{\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f176\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O Angel of Christ, my holy guardi
an and protector of my soul and body, forgive me all wherein I have sinned this day, and deliver me from all opposing evil of mine enemy, lest I anger my God by any sin. Pray for me, a sinful and unworthy servant, that thou mayest show me forth worthy of 
the kindness and mercy of the All-holy Trinity, and of the Mother of my Lord Jesus Christ, and of all the saints. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6953665 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 Then, the Kontakion of the Theotokos:
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par To Thee the Champion Leader, we thy servants dedicate a feast of victory and of thanksgiving, as 
ones rescued out of sufferings, O Theotokos; but as thou art one with might which is invincible, from all dangers that can be, do thou deliver us, that we may cry to thee: Rejoice, thou Bride unwedded!
\par 
\par Most glorious Ever-Virgin, Mother of Christ God, present our prayer to thy Son and our God, that through thee our souls may be saved
\par 
\par All my hope I place in thee, O Mother of God: keep me under thy protection.
\par 
\par O Virgin Theotokos, disdain not me a sinner, needing thy help and thy protection, and have mercy on me, for my soul hath hoped in thee.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6953665 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 Then the prayer of St. Joannicius: 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f176\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
My hope is the Father, my refuge is the Son, my protection is the Holy Spirit: O Holy Trinity, glory to Thee.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The end of the prayers approaching sleep. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid13046292 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13046292 {\f1\fs32\insrsid13046292 ----------
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid13046292 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Here, the Order of Great Compline is resumed: 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Glory to Thee, O God, our hope, glory to Thee. 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. Lord, have mercy.}{
\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6953665  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Father, bless.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The priest saith aloud, while we prostrate ourselves to the earth (except on Fridays, when the lesser dismissal is used:) 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  O Master plenteous in mercy, O Lord Jesus Christ our God: Through the intercessions of our immaculate Lady The
otokos and Ever-virgin Mary; through the power of the precious and life-giving Cross; through the mediations of the honorable, heavenly Bodiless Hosts, of the honorable, glorious Prophet, Forerunner, and Baptist John; of the holy glorious, and all-praised
 apostles; of the holy, glorious, and victorious martyrs; of our holy and God-bearing fathers, }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (the patron saint of the temple)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 ; of the holy and Righteous Ancestors of God Joachim and Anna; of 
}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (the Saints of the day)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  and of all the saints: make our prayer a
cceptable; grant us the remission of our sins; shelter us with the shelter of Thy wings; drive away from us every enemy and adversary; make our life peaceful, O Lord; have mercy on us and on Thy world, and save our souls, for Thou art good and the Lover o
f mankind.
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\i0\insrsid7473308 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain 
\s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 The Rite of Forgiveness 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then, making a prostration, the priest saith to the brethren (sisters, congregation):
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Bless, }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (holy master and) }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 holy fathers }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (mothers)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
 and brethren, and forgive me a sinner, all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and through all my senses. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And the brethren (sisters) (congregation) reply: 
\par }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 May God forgive and have mercy on thee, holy father. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And they make a prostration, asking this forgiveness:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par Bless me, holy father, and forgive all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and thought, and in all my senses, and pray for me a sinner. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Through His grace may God forgive and have mercy on us all. 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7354112 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7354112 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And he saith this Ectenia:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest: }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 Let us pray for the Orth
odox episcopate of the Russian Church; for our lord the Very Most Reverend Metropolitan N., First Hierarch of the Russian Church Abroad; for our lord the Most Reverend (Archbishop or Bishop N., whose diocese it is) and all our brethren in Christ. 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Lord, have mercy}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 . (}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 
Quietly, slowly, and repeatedly, until the petitions are finished )
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  For the suffering Russian land and its Orthodox people both in the homeland and in the diaspora, and for their salvation; for this land, its authorities and armed
 forces, and for every Christian land. 
\par For them that hate us and them that love us. 
\par For them that are kind to us and them that serve us. 
\par For them that have asked us unworthy ones to pray for them. 
\par For the deliverance of the imprisoned. 
\par For our fathers and brethren that have passed on before us. 
\par For those sailing upon the sea. 
\par For those bedridden in infirmities. 
\par Let us pray for the abundance of the fruits of the earth. 
\par And for every Orthodox Christian soul. 
\par Let us bless pious kings (rulers), Orthodox hierarchs, and the founders of this holy habitation. 
\par Our parents, and all that have passed on before us, our fathers, brethren, and the Orthodox here and everywhere laid to rest. 
\par Let us say also for ourselves. 
\par Choir: Lord, have mercy. }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Thrice 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  For the sake of the intercessions of Thy most pure Mother of }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (the patron saint of the temple), }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
and all the saints, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us. 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Amen.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6953665 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 
\par And we venerate the holy icons and receive a blessing from the priest (superior) (bishop).
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7354112 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7354112 ----------
\par ----------
